Spring Boot is a module of the Spring Framework. 
It is used to create stand-alone, production-grade Spring Based Applications with minimum efforts.
It is developed on top of the core Spring Framework.
There are four layers in Spring Boot are as follows:
  Presentation Layer
  Business Layer
  Persistence Layer
  Database Layer



Profiles allow different configurations for different environments such as:
Development 
Testing 
Production 
Each profile can have its own database, logging level, and server settings.
Configuration Files
application.properties
application-dev.properties
application-test.properties
application-prod.properties
Example
spring.profiles.active=dev
When the active profile is dev, Spring Boot loads:
application-dev.properties
Benefits
Separate configurations for each environment 
Easier deployment 
Better security 
Cleaner configuration management





